==== Diurnal and Circadian Patterns

- *Drug works in morning but not evening:* The targeted system has circadian variation in tone. NE levels peak in morning — if atomoxetine works only in AM, the NE system has sufficient endogenous activity to potentiate reuptake inhibition, but evening NE levels are too low. Diagnostic: NE deficiency is absolute in the evening, partial in the morning.
- *Drug works in evening but not morning:* The system's pathology is masked by morning sympathetic activation. If LDN only reduces pain at night, the pain mechanism is mast-cell-driven (nocturnal degranulation), not structural.
- *Drug loses efficacy at specific times:* Diurnal pattern aligned with cortisol rhythm (cortisol nadir at midnight → drug fails at 2--4 AM). The drug's mechanism depends on endogenous cortisol for permissive effect. Consistent with HPA axis dysfunction.
